article.headline: IPFW 72, N. Dakota St. 69
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- DeWitt Scott scored 15 points and IPFW overcame a 12-point halftime deficit on its way to a 72-69 victory over North Dakota State Thursday night. North Dakota State led 68-61 with 3:37 remaining when the Mastodons (8-15) went on a 9-1 run, taking the lead on two free throws by Jakari Johnson with 44 seconds remaining. Scott then made two free throws with seven seconds left to give IPFW a three-point lead. A 3-point attempt by North Dakota State's Mike Nelson at the buzzer was blocked by Demetrius Johnson. Nelson led the Bison (14-7) with 23 points on 9-of-14 shooting. Ben Woodside had 16 points and Andre Smith added 13 points for North Dakota State. The Bison shot 16-of-32 (50 percent) from the floor in the first half and led 39-27 at halftime. Jaraun Burrows had 13 points and seven rebound for IPFW and Tyler Best scored 12 points.
